`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"Introduction"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:'IIT Delhis summer intake is prized for its proximity to policy circles, industry labs, and national research centers in the NCR. The 2026 cohort will again be faculty-driven, with select centralized forms appearing for specific departments. Treat every date and stipend figure noted here as "Expected / Indicative"they mirror 2024/2025 patterns and help you plan outreach before official circulars arrive.'}),`
`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"About the Institute"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"Situated in Hauz Khas, IIT Delhi consistently ranks at the top for engineering and design education, backed by centers such as CARE (AI/ML), Kusuma School of Biological Sciences, and Bharti School of Telecom. Its industrial research park and startup culture mean interns often see live deployments rather than academic-only prototypes. For a macro view, compare peers at the IIT internships hub to understand where Delhi stands on domains and funding."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"Overview of Summer Internship Programme 2026"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"Expect a 68 week program anchored by faculty-led projects across engineering, design, applied sciences, and policy-tech. Interns typically start in late May, spend the first week aligning scope, and then build toward a working demo or technical note. Certificates are standard; credit transfer is uncommon. Labs sometimes extend offers into semester-long projects or paid research assistantships for strong performers."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"Internship Domains / Research Areas Offered"}),`
`,n.jsxs(e.ul,{children:[`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Computer Science & AI: trustworthy AI, language and vision models, distributed systems, formal methods."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Electrical & Communication: RF systems, 5G/6G testbeds, signal processing, VLSI, embedded hardware."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Mechanical & Design: robotics, haptics, additive manufacturing, biomechanics, human-centered product design."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Civil & Environmental: smart infrastructure, transportation analytics, hydrology, air quality modeling."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Chemical & Materials: process simulation, membranes, energy materials, polymer engineering."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Textile & Fibre: smart textiles, composites, functional materials."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Biotechnology & Bioinformatics: biomaterials, computational genomics, medical devices."}),`
