`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Degree: B.Tech/B.E./B.S./Dual/M.Tech/M.S students from accredited institutions."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Year: Priority for 3rd/4th year undergraduates; competitive PG students welcome."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"CGPA: Past shortlists often start near 8.0 (expected) but vary by lab and evidence of fit."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Branches: Wide open; certain labs insist on prerequisites (e.g., signals, probability, mechanics)."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Nationality: Primarily Indian students; international applicants may be considered via MoUs or exchange."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.li,{children:"Additional filters: Prior project alignment carries more weight than generic achievements."}),`
`]}),`
`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"Who Should Apply"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"Apply if you can show relevance to an IIT Delhi lab in one email: recent coursework, a portfolio artifact with results, and a clear statement of what you will build in 68 weeks. Policy-tech and design labs appreciate user research or field-study evidence; systems and hardware labs look for reproducible experiments or schematics. If your college calendar clashes, clarify availability up front to avoid last-minute drops."}),`
