`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:'IIT Palakkad attracts summer applicants because its labs blend core engineering with translational work tied to industry and national missions. This playbook focuses on how to win a seat in 2026: where to look, when to outreach, and how to avoid the common mistakes that sink otherwise strong profiles. Any date or stipend notes marked as "Expected / Indicative" mirror recent cycles and help you move early; update your plan when official circulars post.'}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"If you have limited time, prioritize three moves: (1) shortlist labs and write lab-specific pitches; (2) ship one fresh artifact or small reproduction per target lab; (3) prepare logistics (NOC, hostel plan, travel) so you can accept quickly. These three steps alone raise conversion dramatically versus generic CV blasts."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"About the Institute"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"IIT Palakkad operates in Palakkad, Kerala, giving interns access to regional industries and research ecosystems. The campus hosts active centers spanning AI/ML and data, Systems and control, Power and energy and collaborates with government and industry sponsors. If you are comparing across the IIT system, anchor your choices with the IIT internships hub to see where this institute leads on depth, facilities, and sponsored work."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"Because the institute is embedded in Palakkad, interns can tap into nearby industry partners, field sites, and alumni-led startups. This often translates to problem statements with real datasets or hardware constraints rather than purely academic exercises."}),`
